<p>In these two sentences there are two new words. <strong>â€œkagakuâ€</strong> means "science", and <strong>â€œkurikettoâ€</strong> means "cricket". Some other words which might be useful to mention are <strong>â€œsakkaâ€</strong> which means "football/soccer" and <strong>â€œgakuseâ€</strong> which means "student".</p>
<p>Knowing about the word student, now I could say:</p>
<p class="english">My younger brother is a student but my older brother is not a student.</p>
<p class="english-romaji">Watashi no oto-to wa gakusei desu ga, oni-chan wa gakusei dewa arimasen.</p>
<p class="written-japanese">ã‚ãŸã—ã€€ã®ã€€å¼Ÿã•ã‚“ã¡ã‚ƒã‚“ã€€ã‚ã€€ãŒãã›ã„ã€€ã§ã™ã€€ãŒã€ãŠã«ã„ã¡ã‚ƒã‚“ã€€ã‚ã€€ãŒãã›ã„ã€€ã§ã‚ã€€ã‚ã‚Šã¾ã›ã‚“</p>
